Description:
Description
Do you believe that everyone deserves access to affordable, quality healthcare? Are you driven by creativity, bold ideas, and disruptive innovation? Are you inspired by exceptionally talented, diverse, impact-oriented colleagues? Do you thrive in a dynamic, high-growth, fast-paced environment? Are you fed-up with the status quo of foreign assistance in the health sector? Then consider a job with ThinkWell. ThinkWell is an emerging health systems development organization that is in a major growth phase. Determined to transcend the status quo, ThinkWell was founded in 2011 to provide bold, creative, and practical solutions to helping low- and middle-income countries achieve universal health coverage. 
The Senior Pricing Specialist reports to the Program Finance Manager and works closely with Contracts, Administrators, Design Lab (business development), Operations and Finance groups to lead compliant cost/price strategies and cost/price proposals in response to diverse funders including public entities and commercial clients. The Senior Pricing Specialist is accountable for the accuracy, completeness, and compliance of the cost/price proposal and must develop working knowledge of applicable government and commercial contracts regulations. S/he also engages within and across teams globally as needed, engages with external stakeholders and may manage external vendors or providers.Responsibilities Include: 
Lead/Develop cost/price model, budget narrative, and price strategy

Prepare and review complex contract/subcontract budgets, task orders and pipeline analyses

Prepare/present management briefings

Analyze RFPs and ensure proposal pricing requirements are met

Apply pricing concepts, tools, and techniques using Excel or other funder templates to develop timely and appropriate cost/price worksheets to support proposal responses

Ensure that all cost estimates are justified and supported

Complete all cost requirements identified in new business solicitations

Establish and coordinate cost proposal schedules; monitor schedule and resolve problems

Assist negotiating teams in preparing offers and counter-offers and make recommendations on the financial impact of terms and conditions trade-offs

Maintain a negotiation audit trail of changes/adjustments from initial proposal through final price agreement

Serve as a consultant and spokesperson regarding proposal/pricing matters of major significance

Interface with clients, senior management, peer staff, subcontractors, and all other relevant internal and external entities as necessary to prepare, negotiate, and finalize costing activities

Support internal and external pre-award and post-award audit requests. Update proposal as required

Calculate proposed returns for new business proposals and articulate risks and levers of profitability for senior management team

Serve as a cost reviewer of pricing activities prepared by other staff

Support delivery of the pricing training program (Proposal Budget) for staff members

Coach staff as needed on pricing and cost resolutions for proposals with USAID and non USAID clients

Provide formal and informal (1:1) guidance and mentorship on challenging pricing issues
 We Are:ThinkWell core values are our fundamental organizational guiding principles.  They define our corporate culture, influence our behavior at work and help us achieve our mission.  Our values are:Think bigInfluence the conversationEmpower othersBe exceptionalAlways questionRelate authenticallyEvolve by learningYou Are:ThinkWell core competencies are foundational skills and behaviors that align with our values and are expected of all employees.
An entrepreneurial, results-oriented ‘do-er’ with a willingness to take risk, think big and challenge conventional wisdom.
A change maker who reaches independent judgement with an open mind, influences the conversation, and seeks innovation.
Able to help create an empowering environment in which everyone feels free to take initiative, be accountable and fail intelligently (learn from mistakes).
A collaborative colleague who engages constructively with people from different cultures, orientations, and perspectives and maintains positive relations in a virtual world.
Principally motivated by a growth mindset, meaning the pursuit of knowledge, experience, and self-improvement.  You always question and continuously learn.Authentic, honest, direct, self-aware and open to giving and receiving feedback.
Requirements

BA/BS and 7+ years experience or graduate degree and 5+ years experience;

Knowledge of US Government funded projects and technical assistance contracting procedures;

Experience pricing cost proposals to respond to RFPs from different US Government Agencies and/or other International Donors;

Experience working in international development;

Pricing cost proposals specifically for USAID or DOD will be a plus;

Experience preparing complex budgets in Excel for multi-year cost proposal submissions;

Advanced proficiency with spreadsheets (e.g., pivot tables, charts, Vlookups) and other MS Office applications;

Ability to handle multiple tasks in a fast-paced, deadline-oriented environment;

Ability to interface with all levels of management is essential;

 Excellent oral, written, analytical, and presentation skills;

 Ability to work independently and as a team player, and to manage projects from inception to completion;

 Experience with USG rules, regulations and FAR/OMB.  USAID, CDC, private foundation and corporation contracts experience;

 Adept at communicating technical information to non-technical audiences;

 A team player, motivated to provide subject matter expertise with a collaborative, customer service orientation; 

 A thoughtful systems thinker with grounded, pragmatic understanding of the complexities of our work;

Demonstrated ability to engage effectively with external vendors and stakeholders;

 Full English fluency, second language a plus; 

 Outstanding cross-cultural communication skills, including the ability to relate respectfully with staff at all levels, ages, genders, nationalities and orientations as well as across work areas.
